article.description: Nick Shafnisky accounted for 346 total yards and four touchdowns and Dominick Bragalone ran for a career-high 192 yards and three touchdowns leading Lehigh past Fordham 58-37 on Saturday.
article.headline: Shafnisky's outburst sends Lehigh past Fordham 58-37
article.linkText: Shafnisky's outburst sends Lehigh past Fordham 58-37
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- Nick Shafnisky accounted for 346 total yards and four touchdowns and Dominick Bragalone ran for a career-high 192 yards and three touchdowns leading Lehigh past Fordham 58-37 on Saturday. Shafnisky threw for 238 yards and a touchdown on 10 for 18 passing and had 13 carries for 108 yards and three scores, tying his career-high for rushing touchdowns. In the first quarter, Bragalone scored on a 19-yard run and Shafnisky found Derek Knott for an 84-yard touchdown two minutes later. Kevin Anderson put Fordham on the board when he ran in from 3-yards out to cap a 10-play, 91-yard drive to make it 13-6. But after the teams traded field goals, Lehigh scored three straight touchdowns to make it 37-9 at halftime. Bragalone had a 70-yard touchdown run 55 seconds before halftime. Anderson threw for 285 yards and three touchdowns for Fordham (5-3, 2-1). Chase Edmonds ran for 182 on 24 carries for the Rams.
